title: Bill Chase - Chase (1971)
description:
The self-titled first album from Chase, featuring trumpet player Bill Chase.  Bill Chase stands alone in the pantheon of jazz trumpet players and arrangers, not only for the amazing power and control his playing demonstrates but also for his melding of Jazz and pop/rock in one genre.  Truly one of the greatest trumpet players of the fusion era.

Track Listing:
1. Open up Wide
2. Livin' in Heat
3. Hello Groceries
4. Handbags and Gladrags
5. Get It On
6. Boys and Girls Together
7. Invitation to a River
